< body[1467]	Appendix A -Privacy & Data Handling
< body[1468]	Rule 36 - User data and privacy
< body[1469]	The site captures personal data at four moments: questionnaire, plan-delivery sign-up, visit booking, and BES conversation.
< body[1470]	At every capture point, the user must see the privacy notice and give explicit consent before any data is stored. Compliance with the Mexican LFPDPPP (Ley Federal de Protecci6n de Datos Personales en Posesi6n de los Particulares) is mandatory.
< body[1471]	Data is stored in the client's system, not in separate web-side systems.
< body[1472]	Health data (weight, height, medical conditions, medication use) requires additional, specific consent.
< body[1473]	WhatsApp reminder consent (Rule 3.2) is captured separately from the general privacy consent, with explicit opt-in.
< body[1474]	The user can request deletion of their data at any time, and the request is honored within the timeframes set by the applicable regulation.
< body[1478]	Appendix B -Out-of-Scope Pages
< body[1479]	Rule 37 - Pages explicitly out of scope
< body[1480]	To prevent confusion, the following pages do not exist on the site and are explicitly out of scope:
< body[1482]	Help Center with article cluster. Operational FAQs (cancel, freeze, switch club) are handled by BES. Articles on exercise or nutrition live in the Journal.
< body[1483]	A page for each FitKidz activity. All 34 activities live within the FitKidz hub, organized by age range, discipline, and club availability per Rule 30. There is no individual page per activity.
< body[1484]	A page per trainer. Personal Training has one page, with no individual trainer profiles.
< body[1485]	Studio Polanco or any other boutique studio as a separate entity. They do not exist as a sub-brand on the site.
< body[1486]	Online membership checkout. Per Rule 22, the site does not sell memberships
< body[1487]	transactionally; conversion is via.
