> body[1409]	Part 6 -Edge Cases & Error States
> body[1410]	This part documents what the site does when the happy path fails. Every behavior described here must be implemented and verified before launch.
> body[1411]	6.1 - Geolocation permission denied or unavailable
> body[1412]	Trigger: the browser denies the geolocation permission prompt, or the user is on a device or network that does not return a coordinate.
> body[1413]	Behavior: the system does not prompt repeatedly. The user lands on Home with the (Tu Club ideal) flow opened in capture mode (PS+ P9 manual entry). A non-intrusive notice explains that
> body[1414]	the user can enter their location manually or browse the full club list at.
> body[1414]/txbx[0]/p[0]	/ clubes/
> body[1416]	- External search inferred a location not in the 49-club roster
> body[1417]	Trigger: the user searches(no Sports World club exists in Tijuana).
> body[1417]/txbx[0]/p[0]	gimnasio Tijuana
> body[1419]	Behavior: the user lands on Home, not on a club page. A neutral notice (( No tenemos club en Tijuana)) and a fallback offers to search for the closest club by manual ZIP entry, or browse the full club list. The system does not auto-pick a far club.
> body[1420]	- SEPOMEX autocomplete service unavailable
> body[1421]	Trigger: the SEPOMEX endpoint is down or the user's network blocks it.
> body[1422]	Behavior: P9 falls back to a free-text input with looser validation. The user can submit a neighborhood or city name typed by hand. The system later normalizes the input server-side.
> body[1423]	- Form validation errors Behavior:
> body[1424]	Errors appear inline immediately under the offending field, in Spanish (Mexico), with the same tone and typography as the rest of the site.
> body[1425]	No error blocks the user from editing other fields.
> body[1426]	On submission of a form with errors, the page scrolls to the first error and places focus on it for keyboard and screen-reader users.
> body[1429]	- User abandons the questionnaire mid-flow
> body[1430]	Behavior: partial questionnaire state is preserved in
> body[1430]/txbx[0]/p[0]	localSto rage
> body[1432]	after the user has explicitly
> body[1434]	accepted the privacy notice (Rule 36). When the user returns, the questionnaire offers to resume from the last answered question. If the user has not accepted the privacy notice, no state is preserved.
> body[1435]	- Health disclaimer rejected
> body[1437]	Trigger: in the (Bajar de peso)flow (or rehabilitation hub), the user is shown the health-disclaimer modal and declines.
> body[1438]	Behavior: the user does not receive the personalized weight-loss plan. They receive a non-clinical generic plan instead, with a clear explanation that personalized recommendations require accepting the disclaimer. No data is captured beyond what the user has already entered.
> body[1439]	- BES asked an out-of-scope question
> body[1440]	Trigger: the user asks BES for medical diagnosis, billing changes that require human handling, or a service the site does not offer.
> body[1441]	Behavior: BES redirects to the relevant hub or offers (Hablar con un asesor humano ). It never fabricates an answer. Out-of-scope categories include deep health questions, account-level financial actions, and any commitment about future pricing or promotions.
> body[1442]	- Club catalog or booking API unavailable
> body[1443]	Trigger: the upstream booking API is down, or the club-catalog endpoint times out.
> body[1444]	Behavior:
> body[1445]	Live data per club (Rule 12) -operating hours, phone, email, class catalog, schedule - defaults to the last successfully cached values.
> body[1446]	A visible notice on the affected pages explains that schedules may be outdated and asks the user to confirm by phone.
> body[1447]	The (Agenda tu visi ta guiada) button remains operational but in a degraded mode that captures the lead and contacts the user back manually within one business day, instead of offering a real-time slot.
> body[1449]	- Search query has multiple competing inferences
> body[1450]	Trigger: the user searches (yoga Polanco bajar de peso) (a class+ a location+ a goal).
> body[1451]	Behavior: see Rule 17. Pl wins over P9 wins over P4. For this example, the user lands on the ( Bajar de peso) hub with P9 pre-filled to(Polanco). P4 is not pre-filled (goal-driven landing overrides class-driven landing).
> body[1452]	- Stale plan returning user
> body[1453]	Covered by Rule 34. After 60 days, the user is shown a non-blocking refresh prompt.
> body[1455]	- JavaScript disabled or older browser
> body[1456]	Behavior: the site degrades gracefully. Server-rendered content is fully readable. The drawer becomes a static link list. The questionnaire and BES are unavailable in their interactive form, but their entry points show a graceful notice and direct the user to (Agenda tu visi ta guiada),
> body[1458]	which works server-side. The alternative.
> body[1458]/txbx[0]/p[0]	/bes
> body[1459]	fallback URL provides a server-rendered chat-like
> body[1461]	- Slow connection or data-saver mode
> body[1462]	Behavior: hero videos use a poster image fallback. Below-the-fold images use•
> body[1462]/txbx[0]/p[0]	loading= 11 lazy 11
> body[1463]	The site uses progressive enhancement so that the first meaningful paint is text and image, not a
> body[1464]	blocking video. Animation respects themedia query.
> body[1464]/txbx[0]/p[0]	prefers-reduced-motion
> body[1466]	- Empty result set on amenity or club lists
> body[1467]	Trigger: the user filters amenity X by city Y, and no club in city Y has amenity X.
> body[1468]	Behavior: the empty state is not silent. A short message explains that the combination has no match, and offers two options: (a) the closest club that has the amenity, regardless of city, and (b) the closest amenity to the user's city, regardless of club.
> body[1471]	Appendix A -Privacy & Data Handling
> body[1472]	Rule 36 - User data and privacy
> body[1473]	The site captures personal data at four moments: questionnaire, plan-delivery sign-up, visit booking, and BES conversation.
> body[1474]	At every capture point, the user must see the privacy notice and give explicit consent before any data is stored. Compliance with the Mexican LFPDPPP (Ley Federal de Protecci6n de Datos Personales en Posesi6n de los Particulares) is mandatory.
> body[1475]	Data is stored in the client's system, not in separate web-side systems.
> body[1476]	Health data (weight, height, medical conditions, medication use) requires additional, specific consent.
> body[1477]	WhatsApp reminder consent (Rule 3.2) is captured separately from the general privacy consent, with explicit opt-in.
> body[1478]	The user can request deletion of their data at any time, and the request is honored within the timeframes set by the applicable regulation.
> body[1482]	Appendix B -Out-of-Scope Pages
> body[1483]	Rule 37 - Pages explicitly out of scope
> body[1484]	To prevent confusion, the following pages do not exist on the site and are explicitly out of scope:
> body[1486]	Help Center with article cluster. Operational FAQs (cancel, freeze, switch club) are handled by BES. Articles on exercise or nutrition live in the Journal.
> body[1487]	A page for each FitKidz activity. All 34 activities live within the FitKidz hub, organized by age range, discipline, and club availability per Rule 30. There is no individual page per activity.
> body[1488]	A page per trainer. Personal Training has one page, with no individual trainer profiles.
> body[1489]	Studio Polanco or any other boutique studio as a separate entity. They do not exist as a sub-brand on the site.
> body[1490]	Online membership checkout. Per Rule 22, the site does not sell memberships
> body[1491]	transactionally; conversion is via.
